{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38131514-7a80-4d5b-9feb-7a27a1896a47","content":"No files found in the workspace — so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only required change** is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`. All existing `{Binding ...}` expressions are automatically compiled against that type.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**2. Enable strict mode in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat invalid compiled bindings as build errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this, if you typo a property (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`), the build will **fail** with an error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n## Key Rules\n\n| Scenario | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| Binding to ViewModel props | `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the page |\n| Binding inside a `DataTemplate` | Put `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` element itself |\n| Need to opt out for one binding | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element (e.g., for `RelativeSource` bindings) |\n\nThat's it — `x:DataType` enables compilation, and `MauiStrictXamlCompilation` turns warnings into errors.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f46b59f-2f16-45ce-be6d-780e0e775771","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no existing files. The user is asking me to show them how to convert their page. Since there's no actual file to edit, I'll provide a clear explanation with code examples.","outputTokens":737},"id":"d05cce20-3044-4d86-8403-e2074c0ec8b3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:22:16.679Z","parentId":"3016cfc8-16cf-4337-b45c-8a62626860a6"}
